HOUSE RESOLUTION 61
By Garrett
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend James "Coach
Ballgame" Lowe for his outstanding contributions
to youth baseball and his selection as a speaker
at the 2025 Tennessee Governor's Prayer
Breakfast.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this legislative body should recognize those
individuals who have dedicated their careers to enriching the lives of young people through
sports and character development; and
WHEREAS, James "Coach Ballgame" Lowe has devoted his career to coaching over
100,000 children worldwide, instilling in them a love for baseball and the invaluable life lessons
the sport imparts; and
WHEREAS, a distinguished athlete in his own right, Coach Ballgame was a four-year
starter and All-Ivy League outfielder at Brown University, demonstrating exceptional skill and
commitment to the sport; and
WHEREAS, serving as the Lead Ambassador for Major League Baseball's (MLB) Play
Ball Program, he has brought his unique approach to prestigious venues such as the White
House, Cooperstown, and MLB All-Star Game and World Series events, captivating young
players with humor, nicknames, and memorable catchphrases; and
WHEREAS, through his National Sandlot Tour, Coach Ballgame has visited over 100
cities across North America, transforming the culture of youth baseball by prioritizing
engagement and character development; and
WHEREAS, through Coach Ballgame University, he provides baseball clinics, summer
camps, and coaching education programs that empower youth coaches to lead their teams
effectively with the Coach Ballgame Playbook; and
