WHEREAS, Coach Ballgame's mission is to revolutionize youth sports by replacing a
win-at-all-costs mentality with one that celebrates the joy of play and personal growth, thereby
making baseball fun and accessible to all children; and
WHEREAS, in recognition of his remarkable contributions, Coach Ballgame has been
invited to speak at the 2025 Tennessee Governor's Prayer Breakfast, an event that brings
Tennesseans together for fellowship and prayer for the State; and
WHEREAS, his selection as a speaker at this esteemed event is a testament to his
unwavering commitment to youth development and the positive impact he has had on
communities nationwide; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we honor and
commend James "Coach Ballgame" Lowe for his outstanding contributions to youth baseball,
congratulate him on being selected as a speaker at the 2025 Tennessee Governor's Prayer
Breakfast, and extend our best wishes for his continued success in all future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy.
